lass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 20, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104maq1665702743036.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/maq1665702743036.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/maq1665702743036.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"maq1665702743036\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"maq1665702743036__maxpostdatasize_480673\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the maximum size of the content body sent in POST and PUT requests from the\n      client to the server. This can be used to protect the server against Denial of Service (DOS)\n      attacks.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"maq1665702743036__topic_d147449e1_d147450e1_d147451e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"maq1665702743036__p_d147452e1_d147453e1_d147454e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;init-param&gt;\n &lt;param-name&gt;</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">MAXPOSTDATASIZE</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;/param-name&gt;\n &lt;param-value&gt;</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">KiloBytes</var> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">-1 &lt;/param-value&gt;\n &lt;/init-param&gt;</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"maq1665702743036__p_d147455e1_d147456e1_d147457e1\">Default value if omitted: <code class=\"ph codeph\">2048</code> (2 MB)</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"maq1665702743036__topic_d106292e1_d106293e1_d106294e1_d106295e1_d106296e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d393547e79\">Values</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"maq1665702743036__li_d51182e1_d51183e1_d51184e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">KiloBytes</var>—number of kilobytes\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"maq1665702743036__li_d51185e1_d51186e1_d51187e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-1</code> —disable this size check\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"maq1665702743036__topic_d106297e1_d106298e1_d106299e1_d106300e1_d106301e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d393547e100\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"maq1665702743036__p_d147464e1_d147465e1_d147466e1\">For the WRD servlet, it specifies the maximum size of the content body of the POST and PUT requests.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"maq1665702743036__p_d147467e1_d147468e1_d147469e1\">For the SRD servlet, it specifies the maximum size of the content body (that is, the SOAP envelop) of the POST request.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"maq1665702743036__p_d147470e1_d147471e1_d147472e1\">If the size of data in a request is larger than the specified maximum, an HTTP error is returned with HTTP status code 400 in the response, and the WRD error (<code class=\"ph codeph\">400 URD_BAD_REQUEST</code>) is returned and is displayed in a red page.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yda1665702742322.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>web.xml</a><p>Configuration file of the web application.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kzr1665702743110.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface WRD Configuration Errors</a><p>When configuring the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD), you may encounter a variety of error situations, ranging from incorrectly displayed information to failure to connect to the server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jkx1665702743178.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Denial of Service Attack</a><p>A denial of service attack attempts to make a computer resource unavailable to its intended users.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "MAXPOSTDATASIZE Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 20, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies the maximum size of the content body sent in POST and PUT requests from the client to the server. This can be used to protect the server against Denial of Service (DOS) attacks. <init-param> <param-name> MAXPOSTDATASIZE </param-name> <param-value> KiloBytes | -1 </param-value> </init-param> Default value if omitted: 2048 (2 MB) Values KiloBytes —number of kilobytes -1 —disable this size check Description For the WRD servlet, it specifies the maximum size of the content body of the POST and PUT requests. For the SRD servlet, it specifies the maximum size of the content body (that is, the SOAP envelop) of the POST request. If the size of data in a request is larger than the specified maximum, an HTTP error is returned with HTTP status code 400 in the response, and the WRD error ( 400 URD_BAD_REQUEST ) is returned and is displayed in a red page. Related Links web.xml Configuration file of the web application. Uniface WRD Configuration Errors When configuring the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD), you may encounter a variety of error situations, ranging from incorrectly displayed information to failure to connect to the server. Denial of Service Attack A denial of service attack attempts to make a computer resource unavailable to its intended users. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}